5:
Hey, Kohane. This mountain's where
you grew up, right? What's it like to
be back?
8:
Mmm... Guess it's nice, but I feel like
the city life really suits me better,
y'know?
12:
That's debatable. Either way, don't
mind our errands. You should go
visit home. I'm sure your master
would want to see you.
15:
Nope, not happening! He'd just
laugh.
18:
"Back again so soon, Kohane? You
always did come runnin' straight
back to me, no matter how many
times I tried ta give ya to human
foster parents."
19:
"Don't tell me ya missed me THAT
much."
23:
So I ain't goin' back until that smug
old tengu comes cryin' ta ME!
35:
Nghh, forget it! We're all here cause
Alk wanted to train, right? Let's go!
36:
There's this place Master used to
bring me all the time. You're gonna—
39:
Tch. That blasted tengu's gonna PAY
for this!
41:
Soon's I find it, I'll put an end to
this—for good!
49:
It's that damn tengu again! Mussed
up my field and pinched my best
crops!
53:
As if! He'd never do somethin' like
that!
58:
If I may ask, are you certain the
tengu is the one who did this?
61:
Dead sure. People seen 'im. Bright
red skin 'n a long nose, just like the
mask on that girl's belt.
66:
No, no, no! That doesn't make sense!
There's no way Master did it!
69: We'll find the real thief! Just you wait!
72:
You will? I'd 'ppreciate it, really, but
them yokai are dangerous, child.
Y'all be careful, hear?
76:
It can't have been him... It can't have
been.
81:
We'll get to the bottom of this,
Kohane.
87:
Whoever did this has sullied the
name of your guardian and teacher.
I will see his honor restored!
97: Back to the scene of the crime!
102:
Hold it! We don't know they're the
thief. It could be anyone!
107:
Nimbus is right. That said, they do
look rather suspicious. There's
something strange about how
they're walking.
119:
*sigh* The way they're wobbling
around, I'd guess they're just—huh?
125:
That settles it! STOP RIGHT THERE,
THIEF!
143:
AAAAAH! Look, I dunno who you think
you are, but I ain't lettin' NO ONE
make us tengu look bad—not even
another tengu!
144:
*sniffle* The villagers all hate us
now, and it's ALL! YOUR! FAULT!
157:
Shh... Calm down and look at him,
Kohane. It's just some drunk in a
mask.
163:
I know it's dark and all, and the nose
DEFINITELY stands out...
174:
It is, but it's also very clearly fake.
This man is no tengu.
177:
Wh-whash yer probmum?! Huh?!
Shcared me havta death, jumpin' at
me an' yellin' outta nowhere!
181:
Oh, uh... Yeah, that's fair. We're sorry
we—
186:
Alk, wait. While we apologize for
startling you, we've heard reports of
a "tengu" trampling and stealing
crops.
189:
What? I ain't—hic—I ain't shtoln
nothin'! Got pleeeenny a veggos at
home, I do.
190:
Think I gots me a secret ammirer!
Heh! Shee, ladely I keep finnin' fresh
vegetal—Vlegtabels!—inna mornin'
after I been drinkin'!
194: I think we have our culprit.
204:
C'mon, we've still got Alk's training. I'll
show ya the place I was talkin' about
yesterday!
208:
Kohane... Are you sure you don't
want to visit home first? We aren't in
a hurry.
212:
Yeah, well neither 'm I! Master would
just nag and poke fun at me.
218:
Suuure. That's convincing, coming
from someone who talks about him
nonstop.
221:
Humph! Looks like she's still bossin'
everyone around and lookin' before
she leaps.
223:
But... Heh. I'm glad she's finally made
herself some friends.
